The paper deals with algorithms for computing edge connectivity in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and computer science. The paper provides new randomized contraction approaches that improve upon existing algorithms for sequential, distributed, and parallel models of computation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Among these, cs.DS and cs.DM seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on algorithmic techniques for graph problems.
